{
  "id": "RLSA-2026:20611",
  "title": "Important: gnutls security update",
  "issued": {
    "date": "2026-05-29 00:00:17"
  },
  "updated": {
    "date": "2026-06-03 00:05:21"
  },
  "severity": "Important",
  "description": "Please update the gnutls packages to provide the GNU Transport Layer Security (GnuTLS) library, which implements cryptographic algorithms and protocols such as SSL, TLS, and DTLS.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n* gnutls: Add more checks to DTLS reassembly (CVE-2026-33846)\n* gnutls: Fix qsort comparator in DTLS reassembly (CVE-2026-42009)\n* gnutls: Fix crashing on an underflow with a DTLS datagram (CVE-2026-33845)\n* gnutls: Fix RSA-PSK identity truncation (CVE-2026-42010)\n* gnutls: Fix case-sensitivity of domain name comparison in name constraints (CVE-2026-3833)\n* gnutls: Fix intersecting empty constraints (CVE-2026-42011)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
